  "prompt": "What is the legislative branch responsible for? What is the publication of the legislative branch?",
  "response": "The legislative branch is primarily responsible for making laws. In addition to its lawmaking functions, it oversees the executive branch, approves budgets, confirms or rejects appointments, and has the power to impeach officials and manage various government functions through its committees and subcommittees.\n\nIn the United States, the main publication of the legislative branch is the \"Congressional Record,\" which provides a comprehensive account of the proceedings and debates of the U.S. Congress. Other important publications include bills and resolutions, committee reports, and hearings, all of which are essential for transparency and keeping the public informed about legislative activities.",
